AI-Driven Smart Blind Turn & Sustainable Campus Optimization System

An integrated IoT + AI solution for accident prevention and smart sustainability management.

 Project Overview

This project presents a real-time blind U-turn accident prevention system integrated with an AI-powered sustainable campus monitoring platform.

It combines IoT sensors, edge computing, and AI analytics to improve road safety while optimizing energy, water, air quality, and waste management across campuses or communities.

The system is modular, scalable, cost-effective, and aligned with Sustainable AI and Green Tech principles.

 Problem Statement : 

High risk of accidents at blind U-turns due to low visibility

Inefficient energy and water usage in campuses

Lack of real-time sustainability monitoring

Poor waste segregation practices

No unified smart monitoring infrastructure

Proposed Solution

The solution integrates two core systems:

1. Smart Blind U-Turn Detection System

Ultrasonic sensors detect vehicles approaching from both sides

ESP32 microcontrollers process sensor data

Wireless communication between both ends

LED STOP indicators and buzzer alerts activated in real-time

Optional solar-powered deployment

When a vehicle is detected on one side → the opposite side receives an immediate STOP warning.

 2. AI-Driven Sustainable Campus Monitoring

Smart energy consumption tracking

Water flow monitoring

Soil & irrigation decision support

Air quality monitoring (PM2.5, CO₂)

AI-based waste classification using computer vision

Central dashboard with actionable insights

